title: Master Software Services Agreement
summary: Northwind Cloud Systems W.L.L. → Qatar Retail Group W.L.L. — platform build, hosting & support
meta: | type: contract | ref: MSA-2026-118 | client: Qatar Retail Group W.L.L. | provider: Northwind Cloud Systems W.L.L. | effective: 2026-07-01 | governing-law: State of Qatar | theme: legal | status: draft

toc:

section: 1. Definitions

text: In this Agreement the following capitalised terms have the meanings set out below. Defined terms apply equally to the singular and plural forms.

def: Agreement | meaning: This Master Software Services Agreement together with all Schedules, Statements of Work and executed amendments
def: Services | meaning: The software development, hosting, and support services described in Schedule A and any Statement of Work issued under this Agreement
def: Deliverables | meaning: All software, source code, documentation, designs and other materials produced by the Provider for the Client under a Statement of Work
def: Statement of Work | meaning: A document signed by both parties that describes a specific package of Services, fees, and timeline; abbreviated SOW
def: Acceptance | meaning: The Client's confirmation, or deemed confirmation, that a Deliverable meets the Acceptance Criteria in the relevant SOW
def: Confidential Information | meaning: Non-public information disclosed by one party to the other, in any form, that is marked confidential or would reasonably be understood as confidential
def: Personal Data | meaning: Any information relating to an identified or identifiable natural person processed under this Agreement
def: Force Majeure | meaning: An event beyond a party's reasonable control, including war, natural disaster, and nationwide network or power failure, but excluding inability to pay
def: Background IP | meaning: Intellectual property owned or licensed by a party before the Effective Date, or developed independently of this Agreement
def: Foreground IP | meaning: Intellectual property first created in the course of performing the Services
def: Business Day | meaning: A day other than Friday, Saturday, or a public holiday in the State of Qatar
def: Service Credit | meaning: A credit against future fees payable when the Provider fails to meet a Service Level, calculated under Schedule B

section: 2. Parties

text: This Agreement is made on the Effective Date between the following parties, each a "Party" and together the "Parties".

contact: Northwind Cloud Systems W.L.L. | role: Provider | email: legal@northwind.qa | phone: +974 4012 8800 | address: Tower 3, Lusail Marina District, Doha, Qatar | cr: CR-184502 | vat: VAT-300184502
contact: Qatar Retail Group W.L.L. | role: Client | email: procurement@qrg.qa | phone: +974 4498 1200 | address: D-Ring Road, Building 21, Doha, Qatar | cr: CR-099318 | vat: VAT-300099318

section: 3. Scope of Work

text: The Provider shall design, build, host, and support a multi-tenant retail commerce platform (the "Platform") for the Client, as described in Schedule A and detailed in each SOW. Work is delivered in three phases.

sub: 3.1 Phases & Deliverables

| Phase | Description | Key Deliverable | Target Date |
| 1 | Discovery & solution architecture | Architecture & data-model dossier | 2026-08-15 |
| 2 | Platform build & integrations | Production-ready Platform, source code, CI/CD | 2026-12-15 |
| 3 | Hypercare & handover | Runbooks, training, knowledge transfer | 2027-02-28 |

sub: 3.2 Obligations

obligation: Deliver Schedule A scope in full across all three Phases | owner: Provider | by: 2027-02-28 | priority: high
obligation: Provide a named technical Account Lead within five Business Days of the Effective Date | owner: Provider | by: 2026-07-08
obligation: Grant timely access to Client systems, test data, and stakeholders | owner: Client | sla: within 3 Business Days of request
obligation: Nominate an authorised Acceptance signatory for each SOW | owner: Client | by: 2026-07-15
obligation: Maintain a shared risk-and-issue register reviewed at the fortnightly steering call | owner: both | cadence: fortnightly

deadline: Phase 1 acceptance | date: 2026-08-22 | consequence: Phase 2 start gated until acceptance
deadline: Phase 2 acceptance | date: 2026-12-22 | consequence: 1.5% of Phase 2 fees per week of Provider-caused delay, capped at 8%

sub: 3.3 Acceptance

text: The Client shall test each Deliverable against the Acceptance Criteria within ten Business Days of delivery. Deliverables not rejected in writing within that period are deemed Accepted. A rejection must identify the specific failed criteria, and the Provider shall re-submit a corrected Deliverable within ten Business Days at no additional charge.

section: 4. Fees & Payment

text: Fees are fixed per Phase as set out below and are exclusive of VAT, which is charged at the prevailing rate. Hosting and support fees recur monthly in arrears.

metric: Phase 1 — Discovery & architecture | value: 185000 | unit: QAR
metric: Phase 2 — Platform build | value: 1240000 | unit: QAR
metric: Phase 3 — Hypercare & handover | value: 165000 | unit: QAR
metric: Total build fees (excl. VAT) | value: 1590000 | unit: QAR
metric: Managed hosting & support (monthly) | value: 42500 | unit: QAR

text: Invoices are payable [Net 30]{ weight: bold } days from the invoice date. Undisputed amounts unpaid after the due date accrue interest at 1% per month. The Client may withhold a [reasonably disputed]{ italic: true } amount provided it pays the undisputed balance and notifies the Provider in writing within ten Business Days.

deadline: First milestone invoice due | date: 2026-08-30 | consequence: 1% monthly late interest on overdue undisputed amounts

section: 5. Service Levels (SLA)

text: From the production go-live of Phase 2, the Provider shall meet the following Service Levels for the hosted Platform, measured per calendar month and excluding scheduled maintenance notified at least 48 hours in advance.

sla: Platform availability | target: 99.9% monthly uptime | measurement: external synthetic monitoring | credit: 5% of monthly fee per 0.1% below target
sla: P1 incident response | target: 15 minutes | priority: P1 | hours: 24x7 | definition: full outage or data-loss risk
sla: P1 incident resolution | target: 4 hours | priority: P1 | hours: 24x7
sla: P2 incident response | target: 1 hour | priority: P2 | hours: business hours | definition: major function degraded
sla: P2 incident resolution | target: 1 Business Day | priority: P2
sla: Standard change request | target: 5 Business Days | priority: P3

sub: 5.1 Service Credits

text: Service Credits are the Client's sole financial remedy for a Service Level failure, save where the failure also constitutes a material breach. Total Service Credits in any month shall not exceed 30% of that month's hosting and support fee. Service Credits are applied against the next invoice.

metric: Maximum monthly Service Credit | value: 12750 | unit: QAR

section: 6. Intellectual Property

text: This section governs ownership of intellectual property. Nothing transfers ownership of a party's Background IP.

clause: Ownership of Foreground IP | scope: assigned to Client on full payment for the relevant Deliverable | excludes: Provider Background IP and third-party components
clause: Provider Background IP licence | scope: perpetual, worldwide, non-exclusive licence to the Client to use embedded Background IP solely as part of the Deliverables | excludes: standalone resale
clause: Open-source components | scope: used only under licences compatible with the Client's commercial use, listed in an SBOM delivered with each release | excludes: copyleft licences requiring source disclosure of Client applications
clause: Moral rights & attribution | scope: Provider waives assertion of moral rights in the Deliverables to the extent permitted by law

obligation: Deliver a complete Software Bill of Materials (SBOM) with every production release | owner: Provider | cadence: per release
obligation: Escrow the production source code with a mutually agreed agent, updated quarterly | owner: Provider | cadence: quarterly

section: 7. Warranties

text: Each party warrants that it has full authority to enter into this Agreement and that doing so does not breach any other obligation it owes.

warranty: Deliverables conform to the SOW specification and documentation | owner: Provider | period: 90 days from Acceptance | remedy: free repair or re-performance
warranty: Services performed with reasonable skill and care to recognised industry standards | owner: Provider | period: term of Agreement
warranty: No knowingly introduced malware, backdoors, or undisclosed telemetry | owner: Provider | period: perpetual
warranty: Deliverables do not infringe third-party intellectual property | owner: Provider | period: perpetual | remedy: defend, procure a licence, or replace

text: Except as expressly stated, the Provider gives no other warranties and all implied warranties are excluded to the maximum extent permitted by the governing law.

section: 8. Limitation of Liability

clause: Liability cap | scope: each party's aggregate liability is capped at the total fees paid in the 12 months preceding the claim | cap: 12 months fees
clause: Excluded losses | scope: neither party is liable for indirect, consequential, or loss-of-profit damages | excludes: indirect and consequential damages
clause: Uncapped liability | scope: the cap does not apply to death or personal injury, fraud, IP indemnity, or breach of confidentiality

info: The liability cap and exclusions are a fundamental basis of the commercial pricing in Section 4. | type: warning

section: 9. Confidentiality

text: Each party shall keep the other's Confidential Information secret, use it only to perform this Agreement, and protect it with at least the care it applies to its own confidential information. These obligations survive termination for five years, and indefinitely for trade secrets and Personal Data.

clause: Permitted disclosure | scope: to employees and contractors on a need-to-know basis under equivalent confidentiality obligations | excludes: public disclosure
clause: Compelled disclosure | scope: permitted where required by law or regulator, with prompt notice to the disclosing party where lawful

obligation: Return or securely destroy Confidential Information within 30 days of termination, on request | owner: both | by: 30 days post-termination

cite: ISO/IEC 27001:2022 | section: A.5 Information security policies
cite: Qatar Law No. 13 of 2016 | section: Protection of Personal Data Privacy

section: 10. Data Protection & Security

obligation: Process Personal Data only on the Client's documented instructions | owner: Provider
obligation: Apply encryption in transit and at rest, and role-based access control | owner: Provider | standard: AES-256 / TLS 1.2+
obligation: Notify the Client of any confirmed Personal Data breach without undue delay | owner: Provider | sla: within 48 hours of confirmation
obligation: Host all production Personal Data within the State of Qatar unless the Client approves otherwise in writing | owner: Provider

cite: Qatar Law No. 13 of 2016 | section: Cross-border data transfer

section: 11. Term & Termination

text: This Agreement starts on the Effective Date and continues for an initial term of 24 months, renewing automatically for successive 12-month periods unless either party gives 90 days' written notice before the end of the then-current term.

clause: Termination for cause | scope: either party may terminate on 30 days' written notice of a material breach left uncured | excludes: nothing
clause: Termination for insolvency | scope: either party may terminate immediately if the other becomes insolvent or enters liquidation
clause: Effect of termination | scope: the Provider shall provide up to 90 days of paid exit transition assistance and hand over all Deliverables and data in an agreed open format

obligation: Provide an exit transition plan within 15 Business Days of any termination notice | owner: Provider | by: 15 Business Days post-notice

section: 12. Force Majeure

text: Neither party is liable for failure to perform caused by a Force Majeure event, provided it notifies the other promptly and uses reasonable efforts to mitigate. If a Force Majeure event continues for more than 60 days, either party may terminate the affected Services without liability.

section: 13. Governing Law & Disputes

text: This Agreement is governed by the laws of the State of Qatar. The Parties shall first attempt to resolve any dispute by good-faith escalation to their respective senior executives within 15 Business Days.

clause: Dispute escalation | scope: senior-executive negotiation, then mediation, before any formal proceedings
clause: Jurisdiction | scope: the Qatar International Court and Dispute Resolution Centre (QICDRC) has exclusive jurisdiction over unresolved disputes

cite: QICDRC Regulations and Procedural Rules 2022 | section: Part 6 Dispute Resolution

section: 14. General

clause: Entire agreement | scope: this Agreement supersedes all prior discussions and constitutes the entire agreement between the Parties
clause: Variation | scope: no variation is effective unless made by a written amendment signed by both Parties
clause: Assignment | scope: neither party may assign without the other's prior written consent, not to be unreasonably withheld
clause: Notices | scope: notices must be in writing to the addresses in Section 2 and are deemed received on the next Business Day
clause: Severability | scope: if any provision is held invalid, the remainder continues in full force

ref: Schedule A — Detailed Scope of Work | file: schedules/sow-schedule-a.it | rel: schedule
ref: Schedule B — Service Levels & Credits | file: schedules/sla-schedule-b.it | rel: schedule
ref: Schedule C — Data Processing Addendum | file: schedules/dpa-schedule-c.it | rel: schedule

section: 15. Execution

text: By approving below, each signatory confirms they are authorised to bind their organisation and accept the terms of this Agreement. This document is presented pre-seal; it will be sealed and cryptographically signed once all approvals are recorded.

route: sequential
require: legal
require: finance | when: amount > 100000
require: provider-exec
require: client-exec

approve: Legal review complete — terms acceptable | by: Layla Al-Mansour | role: legal | at: 2026-06-20
approve: Commercial terms and fee schedule approved | by: Omar Khalid | role: finance | at: 2026-06-21
approve: Executed for the Provider | by: Sara Petrova | role: provider-exec | at: 2026-06-22
approve: Executed for the Client | by: Fahad Al-Thani | role: client-exec | at: 2026-06-23

